(130, 175, 'Josh Miller', 'gossyouth@gmail.com', '', '66.219.150.202', '2012-10-23 19:46:19', '2012-10-23 19:46:19', 'Powerful post Josiah.  The song "You Won''t Relent" (by Jesus Culture) has been on my mind a lot this past month and connects directly with this topic.  A lyric in the song that has cut me to the core is "You won''t relent until you have it all."  God''s love is in relentless pursuit of our hearts, which exposes both our unwillingness to give it up and the incredible love of our Father.\r\n\r\nThanks for sharing with us.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.8; rv:16.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/16.0', '', 0, 0),
(131, 175, 'josiahsprague', 'josiah.sprague@gmail.com', '', '190.167.67.249', '2012-10-23 19:48:07', '2012-10-23 19:48:07', 'Thanks Josh! That''s a great song! I think I''m going to listen to that tonight. :)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/22.0.1229.94 Safari/537.4', '', 130, 1),
(132, 175, 'Emily Haney', 'monesprit@gmail.com', '', '67.190.72.62', '2012-10-23 19:51:57', '2012-10-23 19:51:57', 'This is the breaking point... my heart aches for you because I know that feeling. It hurts, but let go and look to God and He will lift you up from it. Trust Him, that was my biggest lesson in living in China. Just trust Him. He is good and He is worthy. He has a purpose for you there. It is hard after some of the excitement of the new/weird/different starts to wear off, but what a season of growth! I can see it in your words. Praying for you, brother! - Emily', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_7_4) AppleWebKit/536.25 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/6.0 Safari/536.25', '', 0, 0),
(133, 175, 'josiahsprague', 'josiah.sprague@gmail.com', '', '190.167.67.249', '2012-10-23 19:58:45', '2012-10-23 19:58:45', 'Thanks Emily. I hope you are right about this being a season of growth. It feels like a season of death, and I''m terrified to be here.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/22.0.1229.94 Safari/537.4', '', 132, 1),
(134, 175, 'Jen Confer', 'jbcon02@aol.com', '', '99.3.8.167', '2012-10-23 20:52:08', '2012-10-23 20:52:08', 'We''ve talked a lot at our home groups about the "death of a dream."  We have a dream (a vision) of what we feel that God is calling us to do.  We ready ourselves, pray, seek God''s face, make preparations, and launch out only to see our original vision of ministry (or whatever) vaporize before our eyes.  Death of a dream.  And yet, this is where God steps in...which is what you are experiencing now, I think.  Keep seeking His face.  Listen for His voice in every situation.  He''ll resurrect the dream in His time and in His way and you''ll be amazed.  We''re praying for you here.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:16.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/16.0', '', 0, 0),
(135, 175, 'Caleb', 'calebma777@yahoo.com', '', '70.60.49.62', '2012-10-23 21:06:59', '2012-10-23 21:06:59', 'Thanks for the post Josiah. I want you to know that you are on my prayer list like I said I would do. I hope you do the same for me. Love you brotha!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.7; rv:15.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/15.0.1', '', 0, 0),
(136, 175, 'Uncle Randy', 'spraguer@zoomtown.com', '', '74.215.67.134', '2012-10-23 21:59:09', '2012-10-23 21:59:09', 'Just be aware that He may have even more chiseling to do even after you think you''re at the end.  I''ve been there, soon after my mom remarried.  It was a horrible time (nearly gave up on my faith), but it was all part of the process of taking my eyes off myself and only being able to trust in Christ.  I''m still learning (still very selfish) and it''s been 40 years since that time.  But I wouldn''t trade it for the world.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 9.0; Windows NT 6.1; Win64; x64; Trident/5.0)', '', 0, 0),
(137, 175, '"Tia Jota"', 'afullerton@moody.edu', '', '190.167.95.175', '2012-10-23 22:50:28', '2012-10-23 22:50:28', 'Hey Josiah, thanks for you never ending honesty! Even though life is hard right now, God totally used this blog post to challenge me to surrender all to Him again. Jesus told us that if we want to truly seek Him we have to deny ourselves, pick up our crosses daily, and follow Him (Luke 9:23). That is so hard (and, yes, sometimes painful), but isn''t it so awesome at the same time?! Jesus'' love is better than life itself! Keep on following Him, brother.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_7_5) AppleWebKit/536.26.14 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/6.0.1 Safari/536.26.14', '', 0, 0),
(138, 175, 'Sue Williams', 'suebeth22@speedynet.net', '', '98.17.4.32', '2012-10-24 01:43:07', '2012-10-24 01:43:07', 'For He has satisfied the thirsty soul,\r\nAnd the hungry soul He has filled with what is good. \r\nPsalm 107:9\r\n\r\nJosiah, be filled with His goodness....much more will fit in as you leave your desires behind! \r\n\r\nHang in there....I''m going to pray for you right now!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; rv:15.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/15.0.1', '', 0, 0),
(143, 175, 'Adam', 'ajhorsfall@gmail.com', '', '184.56.23.220', '2012-10-24 11:19:10', '2012-10-24 11:19:10', 'That''s a great passage! We should take a warning from King Asa failure to rely on the Lord for his strength. There are many pragmatic ways to get things done throughout life and some of them are done in wisdom, but the best made plans come to nothing without God''s will. \r\nI like the title of this post. It''s true in lots of places! I can''t be a good husband and dad in my own strength. I can''t be a worship leader in my own strength. I can''t even get up in time to do my devotionals in my own strength sometimes! But like the writers of the Bible I can do all this stuff and more while being carried along by the Holy Spirit. Asa found a way to deal with his political problems in his own strength, but wouldn''t it have been better to be carried along by the Holy Spirit?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; U; Android 2.3.5; en-us; Sprint APA9292KT Build/GRJ90) AppleWebKit/533.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Mobile Safari/533.1', '', 0, 0),
(145, 175, 'Cousin Mike', 'Mijowalsh@gmail.com', '', '75.187.203.116', '2012-10-24 11:48:55', '2012-10-24 11:48:55', 'We are with you in what ever you decide. \r\n\r\nI always think of Jacob who wrestled with God and would not let go until he was blessed.\r\n\r\nThose struggles come big and small as do the blessings.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (iPad; CPU OS 6_0 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/536.26 (KHTML, like Gecko) Mobile/10A403 [FBAN/FBIOS;FBAV/5.0;FBBV/47423;FBDV/iPad2,1;FBMD/iPad;FBSN/iPhone OS;FBSV/6.0;FBSS/1; FBCR/;FBID/tablet;FBLC/en_US]', '', 0, 0),
