(2824, 548, 'wp-svbtle-markdown', 'Lately, it seems like there is never enough time in the day to do all of the things on my plate. Between producing media for Doulos, teaching class, blogging, translating, attending several small groups, making websites, building a small business on the side and trying to keep my education up to date, I do a lot of things. But lately I''ve been dissatisfied; My work is mediocre by my own standards and I''m not accomplishing things that are meaningful to me.\r\n\r\nI want to do better work. I want to accomplish more meaningful things. I want to use my talents more fully. I want to love people better and build deeper relationships. I want to have time to reflect on what I''m doing. I want to use the one life that God has given me to it''s maximum potential.\r\n\r\nI need to focus my energy on doing one thing well rather doing many things with mediocrity. After spending time reflecting on my values and passions, I''ve clarified my personal vocation or calling as the following;\r\n\r\nHelping individuals and organizations serve one another via the web.\r\n\r\nMy current challenge is bring all of the aspects of my life keenly into focus on that calling. My ideal career involves two parts. The first is craftsmanship, and the second is apprenticeship. My vision is a work in progress, but I want to share with you how I see those parts playing out in my near future.\r\n\r\nCraftsmanship\r\nCraftsmanship means using one''s gifts and talents to skillfully create high quality work and design. My vision is to form a business that will craft high quality websites for a variety of clients and to cultivate and increase the market value of those individuals and organizations via the web medium.\r\n\r\nI have already established a small base of six initial clients for this company. While I am very familiar with my craft, I have a lot to learn concerning running a business, so I am currently working with Fourth Water, a local business accelerator in Jarabacoa, and developing a formal business plan.\r\n\r\nApprenticeship\r\nThe word "apprenticeship" is related to the Spanish word "aprender--to learn" and it means learning via practical experience from a skilled professional. I believe that both being an apprentice and having apprentices is vital to quality work and craftsmanship. My vision is to merge my role as a constantly learning professional with my role as a teacher.\r\n\r\nThis past semester I had the opportunity to teach an elective communication class at Doulos Discovery School in Jarabacoa. This coming semester, inspired by my passion for the web and students requesting to learn computer programming, I am developing plans to teach a programming elective for high school and a code club for elementary school. My long term vision is to be able to connect these students with hands on experiences to learn via the business that I am forming.\r\n\r\nThe specifics of this vision are still forming, and there is a long way to go. My desire is that they will continue to become clearer and more focused and that the end result will be a fruitful investment of the time and talents that God has given me.\r\n\r\nI covet your advice, prayers and continued support while this vision evolves and grows. If you''d like to discuss this in more detail, please feel free to contact me, I''d love to share more with you.'),
