ttp://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/46386d94dab711e1bf341231380f8a12_7-300x300.jpg" alt="Praying Mantis" width="300" height="300" /></a>\n\nSo far my schedule has been focused on learning Spanish (which is simultaneously exhilarating and exhausting), and work days at the school. A few of us spent a few hours shoveling gravel, which our bodies are still punishing us for, and I got to spend a lot of time carving wooden signs for some new classrooms. Building things with my hands was a nice change from a 9 to 5 office environment.\n\n<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/50c3fefadde511e19fb4123138101461_7.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-29" title="50c3fefadde511e19fb4123138101461_7" src="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/50c3fefadde511e19fb4123138101461_7-300x300.jpg" alt="Carving signs for the new Doulos classrooms." width="300" height="300" /></a>\n\nThere are other changes from my usual routine that have been a little harder to adjust to, such as how laundry is done here. Some people have fully automatic laundry, as in the states, but it is very common here to do laundry with a semi-automatic washer, and then dry it on the line. It takes more time and patience, and it''s compatible with my usual procrastination when it comes to laundry. Over time I think I will get used to it and value the extra time to think and pray.\n\n<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/b77be87cdc1611e194a422000a1e8aa6_7.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-30" title="b77be87cdc1611e194a422000a1e8aa6_7" src="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/b77be87cdc1611e194a422000a1e8aa6_7-300x300.jpg" alt="Air drying laundry takes a long time." width="300" height="300" /></a>\n\nThere have been both blessings and challenges so far, but by far the best moments I have had in the last few weeks were those of fellowship and worship. In a culture where I feel lost 95% of the time, it is an absolutely amazing sensation of solidarity to realize that we know the same loving father that takes care of all of our needs.\n\n<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/ecebb50cda3911e1aeb3123138150f49_7.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-31" title="ecebb50cda3911e1aeb3123138150f49_7" src="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/ecebb50cda3911e1aeb3123138150f49_7-300x300.jpg" alt="Bi-cultural worship." width="300" height="300" /></a>\n\nThe very though of His love brings rest in a time and place where everything takes intentional effort for me. But I am tired, if you''re one for praying, pray that I would spend more time resting in His love, seeking His presence and listening to and trusting His voice. I have worries, like whether I will be able to communicate well in Spanish, whether I will build strong relationships here, whether all of the support that I need will come in, and whether or not I will excel at my job here.\n\nTo be honest, I spend much less time trusting God than I should. But I am thankful that I am here, with all of my familiar surroundings and comfortable retreats removed, where God''s love is the only comfort that I know. It brings to mind a quote that my Grandma loves to remind me of;\n<blockquote>youths grow weary and tired,\nAnd vigorous young men stumble badly,\n\n<strong>31</strong> Yet those who wait for the LORD\nWill gain new strength;\nThey will mount up <em>with </em>wings like eagles,\nThey will run and not get tired,\nThey will walk and not become weary.</blockquote>\n&nbsp;', 'M New Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-08-06 19:32:34', '2012-08-06 19:32:34', '', 22, 'http://josiahsprague.com/blog/22-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
