(150, 1, '2012-08-30 14:47:37', '2012-08-30 14:47:37', '<blockquote>Consider it all joy, my brethren, when you encounter various trials, knowing that the testing of your faith produces endurance. And let endurance have its perfect result, so that you may be perfect and complete, lacking in nothing. But if any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all generously and without reproach, and it will be given to him. But he must ask in faith without any doubting, for the one who doubts is like the surf of the sea, driven and tossed by the wind.</blockquote>\nIn the last several weeks, since moving to Jarabacoa, my faith has been tested by trials in various aspects of my life. I''m used to being in control of my relationships with others, my responsibilities, my income, and my abilities, but all of those things have been out of my hands in recent weeks. At times I have felt vulnerable to being tossed like a wave in the wind.\n\n[caption id="attachment_145" align="alignnone" width="300"]<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/14479712e8b611e1a74f1231380fcc36_7.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-145" title="Wave at Cabarete" src="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/14479712e8b611e1a74f1231380fcc36_7-300x300.jpg" alt="Wave at Cabarete" width="300" height="300" /></a> A wave being tossed in the wind at Cabarete.[/caption]\n\nThough the wind and waves of my life have been unpredictable lately, I have found incredible peace and security in talking to God about my worries and trusting that <a href="http://bible.us/rom8.28.nasb">He will work all things out for my good</a>. When we trust God, we can ride the wind and the waves with confidence, like the surfers that I saw recently in Cabarete. I know that no matter what direction the winds of life blow, God is in control. Even the trials are used to refine and build my character.\n\n[caption id="attachment_146" align="alignnone" width="300"]<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/edb01d50e8a011e1bf7c22000a1e9ddc_7.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-146" title="Wind Surfers in Cabarete" src="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/edb01d50e8a011e1bf7c22000a1e9ddc_7-300x300.jpg" alt="Wind Surfers in Cabarete" width="300" height="300" /></a> Surfers and Kite Boarders Riding the Wind and Waves in Cabarete[/caption]\n\nBut unless I am feasting daily on the truth of God''s word, I will be lacking the ability to trust God. It is easy for me to forget to <a href="http://bible.us/matt4.4.nasb">fill myself daily with God''s truth</a>. I remember so easily to feed my physical body. (And who wouldn''t with the delicious Dominican food that is so common here?), but it is so much more important for me to feed my spiritual body.\n\n[caption id="attachment_147" align="alignnone" width="300"]<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/bfddc0b4eeac11e1851d22000a1e9dc3_7.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-147" title="Fried Salami Sandwich with Tostones" src="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/bfddc0b4eeac11e1851d22000a1e9dc3_7-300x300.jpg" alt="Fried Salami Sandwich with Tostones" width="300" height="300" /></a> A common Dominican meal; A Fried Salami Sandwich with Tostones. One of my new favorites.[/caption]\n\nI am continuing to learn more and more every day about Dominican culture and language. Every conversation is a learning experience, and I am learning as much about communication itself as I am learning about my new home. What a beautiful thing that God has made us with the ability to communicate and share with one another, and it is so fulfilling when we<a href="http://www.relevantmagazine.com/life/whole-life/are-you-letting-others-define-you"> communicate in a way that honors God</a>.\n\n[caption id="attachment_148" align="alignnone" width="300"]<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/64305cf2f03911e190bd22000a1cdd09_7.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-148" title="Learning to Make Chinola Tea" src="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/64305cf2f03911e190bd22000a1cdd09_7-300x300.jpg" alt="Learning to Make Chinola Tea" width="300" height="300" /></a> Learning to Make Chinola (Passion Fruit) Tea, Combined with a Lesson in Spanish[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_149" align="alignnone" width="300"]<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/1cf9f6b8eeea11e1a4d022000a1d0cc7_7.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-149" title="Home in Jarabacoa" src="http://josiahsprague.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/1cf9f6b8eeea11e1a4d022000a1d0cc7_7-300x300.jpg" alt="Home in Jarabacoa" width="300" height="300" /></a> The house where I am living. My current home.[/caption]\n\nGod is stretching me, and it is good. I am not comfortable, but I am able to rest in His love, and feel at home, confident that He is providing for all of my needs. I am so thankful for this time of growing in faith, and I am excited to see the fruits of this season of my life. Thank you for your continued prayers and <a href="http://josiahsprague.com/support/">support</a>!', 'God Is Stretching Me To Trust Him', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '144-revision', '', '', '2012-08-30 14:47:37', '2012-08-30 14:47:37', '', 144, 'http://josiahsprague.com/blog/144-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
