(852, 1, '2014-05-08 22:02:02', '2014-05-08 22:02:02', 'If you know me at all, you know that I''m a big fan of both Twitter and WordPress. I love how both platforms make it easy for people to share ideas and communicate openly and freely. I love that both serve as a sort of "public square" of the web and support discourse, democracy and free society.\r\n\r\nI''ve been inspired lately by the ways that some websites have integrated Twitter, and I wanted to bring the same kind of integration to WordPress and take it a step further; helping WordPress bloggers to spark discussions and discourse on Twitter and other social media sites with the powerful statements they are already making.\r\n\r\nSo, I made a WordPress plugin that does exactly that. The plugin was mostly inspired by two sources. The first was the toolbar on Medium.com that enables people to tweet or comment on the text they select. The second was <a href="http://storylineblog.com">Donald Miller''s Storyline blog</a>, where he''s been adding "(tweet this)" links to the end of powerful quotes. The plugin is called <a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/quotable/">Quotable</a>, and it brings both of those ideas to WordPress.\r\n\r\nQuotable helps readers share your inspiring content in two ways; first, by highlighting the text that they like and clicking one button to share it on Twitter. Second, by adding a link to the bottom of all the block quotes in a post, that will instantly share it.\r\n<blockquote>\r\nQuotable helps your readers share inspiring quotes from your site and spark engaging dialogue.\r\n</blockquote>\r\nThe plugin really serves two crowds. The readers of WordPress blogs that have the Quotable plugin installed will be able to quickly and easily share quotes that they like, and the authors of WordPress blogs benefit from the increased sharing of their content.\r\n\r\nThe plugin is written in a way that enhances existing features of <a href="https://yoast.com/wordpress/plugins/seo/">Yoast''s WordPress SEO plugin</a>. If a site uses that plugin to define Twitter accounts for the site and it''s authors, those accounts will be mentioned in the tweets created by Quotable, which will encourage new followers and create new readers.\r\n\r\nIf you manage a WordPress site, I''d love it if you <a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/quotable/">give Quotable a try</a>. It''s the first version, and I hope to improve it as time goes on, so I would greatly appreciate your feedback. If you try it and like it, please share it with others. I hope that this plugin not only enhances your site, but also benefits discourse, democracy and free society on the web.', 'I made a thing for WordPress', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '786-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-08 22:02:02', '2014-05-08 22:02:02', '', 786, 'http://josiahsprague.com/786-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(207, 1, '2013-01-12 11:59:09', '2013-01-12 11:59:09', 'If you''ve arrived on this page without first hearing my vision for my ministry at Doulos, I invite you to <a href="http://josiahsprague.com/">read about my vision</a> first.\r\n<h2 id="goal">My Support Goal</h2>\r\nTo keep tuition costs at a minimum for families and sponsors, North American staff raises full support to work at Doulos. <b>I’ll need to raise about $920/mo, which is about $11,000/yr.</b>\r\n\r\nHere’s a breakdown of what I’ll need per month;\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Need</th>\r\n<th>Estimated Amount</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tithe</td>\r\n<td>$92</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Rent</td>\r\n<td>$180</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Food</td>\r\n<td>$165</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cell Phone</td>\r\n<td>$15</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Mail</td>\r\n<td>$5</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Insurance, Taxes and Fees</td>\r\n<td>$193</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Miscellaneous</td>\r\n<td>$45</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>School Loans</td>\r\n<td>$60</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Plane Tickets</td>\r\n<td>$165</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Total</th>\r\n<th>$920</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2 id="give">Ways to Give</h2>\r\nIf you''ve heard my vision and want to be a part of my team of supporters, here''s how you can do that:\r\n\r\n<b>If you want to sponsor me monthly,</b> you can give automatically via direct donation. To do so, download the <a href="http://josiahsprague.com/pdf/JosiahSpragueDonation.pdf">direct donation form</a> and mail it to the <a href="http://josiahsprague.com/support/#address">Minesota Doulos address</a>, below, along with your first check. Alternatively, you can set up your bank account to automatically send a check to that address every month. If you would prefer to donate online, you can set up a monthly donation via PayPal, <a href="http://josiahsprague.com/support/#paypalform">above</a>.\r\n\r\n<b>If you want to support me with a one time donation,</b> you can send a check to the Minesota Doulos address, or donate online via <a href="http://doulosdiscovery.org/support/donate/">the donation page on the Doulos website</a>.\r\n\r\nPlease make all checks payable to <i>Doulos Discovery Ministries</i> and, for tax purposes, please be sure to include a note along with your check indicating that the donation is for Josiah Sprague (it is best if this is a separate note, rather than being written on the memo line).\r\n\r\nPlease send Direct Donation Forms and checks to:\r\n<p id="address">Doulos Discovery Ministries\r\nPO Box 3080\r\nBurnsville, MN 55337</p>\r\n<small><b>Donations are TAX DEDUCTIBLE</b>, as they are made to Doulos Discovery Ministries – a registered 501(c)3 US not-for-profit – then distributed to staff. Receipts are mailed to donors 3 times/year and year-end giving receipts are provided at end of each tax year.</small>', 'Support', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '201-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-01-12 11:59:09', '2013-01-12 11:59:09', '', 201, 'http://josiahsprague.com/blog/201-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
