(352, 1, '2013-04-23 21:17:22', '2013-04-23 21:17:22', 'I''m a web and video craftsman currently living in Jarabacoa in the Dominican Republic and working as the Media Coordinator at <a href="http://doulosdiscovery.org">Doulos Discovery School</a>.\n\nHere''s a quick guide to the stuff you''ll find here;\n\n<a title="My Story" href="http://josiahsprague.com/category/story/"><strong>Journal</strong></a> - Basically the story of my life; everything that I''m doing and learning. For stalkers trying to keep tabs on me.\n\n<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/category/dr/"><strong>Dominican</strong></a> - Stories about life in the Dominican Republic, my work at Doulos, and everything related to that. <a title="Support" href="http://josiahsprague.com/support/">Support me!</a>\n\n<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/category/thinking/"><strong>Thoughts</strong></a> - External processing. AKA preaching from my soapbox.\n\n<a href="http://josiahsprague.com/category/web/"><strong>Web Stuff</strong></a> - Technical, web industry related stuff. #nerdstatus\n<h2>Who I Am</h2>\nIf people only remember two things about my life, they should be this;\n<blockquote>"I am a great sinner, and Christ is a great savior."</blockquote>\nMy take on religion;\n<blockquote>"Love God. Love others. Nothing else matters."</blockquote>\nOn being nice;\n<blockquote>"Love is something more splendid and stern than mere kindness."</blockquote>\nThe way I think;\n<blockquote>"Everything that is alive is changing. People, organizations, ideas, all of it. What is static is dead."</blockquote>\nWhen it comes to the work I do;\n<blockquote>"If I''m going to spend a day cutting down a tree, I''ll spend two thirds of it sharpening my axe."</blockquote>', 'Hi, I''m Josiah Sprague', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '351-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-04-23 21:17:22', '2013-04-23 21:17:22', '', 351, 'http://josiahsprague.com/351-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
