(570, 1, '2013-11-26 13:41:47', '2013-11-26 13:41:47', 'The verse of the day today on YouVersion is Matthew 7:1, the famous "Don''t judge, lest you be judged".\nI have my Bible app set on a Spanish version, and I noticed something about this verse that we often forget in English; this verse is referring to a group of people. If you were from the south, it could be translated, "Hey y''all, don''t judge outsiders, so that they don''t judge y''all."\nI think we fail hugely in this area as the modern church. One of the most common words that I''ve heard outsiders use to describe the church is "judgemental". That''s a huge problem. Judgementalism doesn''t serve anything but the egos of those who are judging, putting them in a place that is anti-Christ and anti-love.\nSo, Church, let''s stop judging others so that others stop judging us--they have every right to do so if we started it.', 'Hey y''all, don''t judge!', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'hey-yall-dont-judge', '', '', '2014-03-03 00:34:17', '2014-03-03 00:34:17', '', 0, 'http://josiahsprague.com/?p=570', 0, 'post', '', 0),
