(759, 1, '2014-03-17 18:41:49', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p dir="ltr">While our students are enjoying a well-deserved break from school, the Doulos campus will still be alive with activity.  In addition to <a href="http://doulosdiscovery.org/opportunities/camp-discovery/">Camp Discovery</a>, Doulos hosts the Spanish Language Institute from June 16th to August 1st. The Spanish Language Institute (SLI) offers up to 7 weeks of intensive Spanish classes, four hours a day with experienced native speakers that will help you achieve fluency. If you''ve been waiting for an excuse to come visit Doulos, this is it!</p>\n&nbsp;\n<p dir="ltr">The Spanish Language Institute was established to prepare individuals to serve in the Dominican Republic and Spanish-speaking communities around the world. SLI forms an important part of our mission at Doulos Discovery School to educate and equip servant leaders. SLI is preparation for communication and mutual understanding. If you are considering or preparing for a service project in Latin America, want to supplement or refresh your Spanish, or simply want to experience life in the mountains of the Cordillera Central and kick back under a mango tree, we welcome you with open arms.</p>\n&nbsp;\n<p dir="ltr">Over the summer, the bilingual campus of Doulos transforms into a Spanish-only zone. For effective language learning, practice and persistence are important, but the real catalyst is immersion. We ask all our students to commit to only speaking Spanish while they are on campus in order to accelerate their learning as well as that of their peers. Agreeing to only speak Spanish is more than just a language-learning tool, but it is a life lesson about the rewards of persistence and dedication. <img alt="edit" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/pzbkWndt9xjHKWrtv29kNEHzCeUkq6L-6p34ac-moTSm7V3myTnTqKprrk4J29syIhfUIdRjCw2Q8IJKm9wUkzyB1EXDga7X9RTAgWP2bPYdryOuNcpv8uv_d288-Q" width="400px;" height="400px;" /></p>\n&nbsp;\n<p dir="ltr">During your time at SLI you will stay with a Spanish-speaking host family, which will help you quickly pick up everyday Spanish used in the home, while your time in class will give you the tools you need to learn proper grammar and pronunciation and increase your understanding. You will also get to participate in cultural workshops, take tours of Jarabacoa and watch and discuss Spanish films with the group. On the weekends, <a href="http://doulosdiscovery.org/opportunities/spanish-language-institute/excursions/">SLI excursions </a>will take you around the island to visit Santo Domingo, 27 Waterfalls, Spirit Mountain Coffee Farm, and Paradise Island among others. Doulos encourages learning inside and outside the classroom and this philosophy extends to SLI. Our desire for students during the excursions is that they can use Spanish for personal enrichment by indulging their curiosity and experiencing the wonders of the Dominican Republic, as well as getting some excellent Spanish practice!</p>\n&nbsp;\n<p dir="ltr">If you want to improve your Spanish while having the experience of a lifetime, we hope you''ll make plans to join us this summer for our Spanish Language Institute. Apply today, tell a friend, and don’t forget to pack your sunscreen!</p>\n&nbsp;', '', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2014-03-17 18:41:49', '2014-03-17 18:41:49', '', 0, 'http://josiahsprague.com/?p=759', 0, 'post', '', 0),
